  "body": "Currently to induct validator to **active status** and exit validator to **withdrawn status**, the biggest bottle neck is having to loop through the entire validator registry and look for the following conditions:\r\n\r\nEligible to active: `validator.activation_epoch > get_entry_exit_effect_epoch(current_epoch) and state.validator_balances[index] >= MAX_DEPOSIT_AMOUNT`\r\n\r\nEligible to exit: `validator.exit_epoch > get_entry_exit_effect_epoch(current_epoch) and validator.status_flags & INITIATED_EXIT`\r\n\r\nThat's O(n) look up and the validator registry length is not small, worst case _16384_, normal case _300K_, worst case _4M_. One way to alleviate this bottle neck is to keep track of a `last_activate_validator_index` and `last_exited_validator_index` , and instead to start the loop at validator 0 `for index = 0; index < len(validator_registry); index++`, we can start at last cached index `for last_activate_validator_index = 0; ; index < len(validator_registry); index++`\r\n\r\nReferences:\r\nhttps://github.com/prysmaticlabs/prysm/blob/master/beacon-chain/core/validators/validator.go#L292\r\nhttps://github.com/prysmaticlabs/prysm/blob/master/beacon-chain/core/validators/validator.go#L308\r\n ",
